cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CY 

This paper deals with the detection of text generated by large-scale language models, which is a topic closely related to natural language processing (NLP) and artificial intelligence (AI). Therefore, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves statistical analysis and hypothesis testing, which are common in machine learning and computational statistics, making cs.LG a likely sub-category as well. The potential misuse of language models for misinformation campaigns also raises concerns about cybersecurity (cs.CR) and ethics (cs.CY), making these sub-categories less likely but still possible.
